---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const updated = "June 20, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title="Data Processing Addendum" description="Renderical's Data Processing Addendum overview.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:24px">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Data Processing Addendum</h1>
      <p class="lead">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top:8px">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <p>This page summarizes the Data Processing Addendum (“DPA”) that forms part of the
      agreement between Renderical, Inc. and customers who process personal data through the
      service. This is a product template and not legal advice; the executable DPA is available
      on request.</p>

      <h2>Roles</h2>
      <p>For recipient and message data you send, you are the data controller and Renderical is
      the data processor, acting on your documented instructions.</p>

      <h2>Processing scope</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Subject matter: delivery, scheduling, and routing of notifications.</li>
        <li>Duration: for the term of your agreement plus configured retention.</li>
        <li>Data subjects: your end-users and recipients.</li>
        <li>Data types: contact identifiers, message content, and engagement events.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Sub-processors</h2>
      <p>We engage vetted sub-processors for hosting and channel delivery under written terms with
      equivalent protections. A current list and change-notification process are available on request.</p>

      <h2>Security & transfers</h2>
      <p>We maintain technical and organizational measures described on our
      <a href="/security">Security page</a>, and rely on Standard Contractual Clauses and data
      residency options for international transfers.</p>

      <h2>Requesting the DPA</h2>
      <p>To execute a DPA, email <a href="mailto:legal@renderical.com">legal@renderical.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
